</caption>
<paragraph blockId="4.[192,802,1644,1851]" pageId="4" pageNumber="3">
The study of the 
<typeStatus box="[390,484,1644,1667]" pageId="4" pageNumber="3">holotype</typeStatus>
of 
<taxonomicName box="[527,657,1644,1667]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Centruroides" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="3" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="eustatius">
<emphasis box="[527,657,1644,1667]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="3">C. eustatius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(temporarily housed at the Instituto de Ecología y Sistemática, 
<collectingRegion box="[192,276,1706,1729]" country="Cuba" name="La Habana" pageId="4" pageNumber="3">Havana</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[290,348,1706,1729]" name="Cuba" pageId="4" pageNumber="3">Cuba</collectingCountry>
) and the specimens recorded herein, and their direct comparison to additional samples of 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Pocock" baseAuthorityYear="1898" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Centruroides" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="3" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="barbudensis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="3">C. barbudensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from other islands (type locality included), confirms that the synonymy proposed by Armas (1983) is correct.
</paragraph>
